<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I decided to give <a href="https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode">FiraCode Mono a try</a>. Since I&#39;d like some extra glyphs I&#39;m actually using the <a href="https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/tree/master/patched-fonts/FiraCode">patched Nerd Font version</a>. </p> <p>I also like to have comment faces italic </p> <pre><code>(custom-theme-set-faces ... ... `(font-lock-comment-delimiter-face ((t (:foreground ,my/comment-colour :slant italic)))) `(font-lock-comment-face ((t (:foreground ,my/comment-colour :slant italic)))) ... ) </code></pre> <p>There is no italic variant of the font though. </p> <p>Is there any way to simulate or fake italics?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/bhrgunatha"> /u/bhrgunatha </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/whf9j0/is_it_possible_to_simulate_italics_for_a_font/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/whf9j0/is_it_possible_to_simulate_italics_for_a_font/">[comments]</a></span>